    "original_title": "Brooklyn: Flatbush Avenue - Myrtle Avenue",
    "text": "Flatbush Avenue Extension, east side, north from Myrtle Avenue to Duffield Street. The buildings on the extreme right are on the east side of Gold Street. View 2 shows some slight changes that have taken place, especially the rebuilt gasoline station and the removal of the diner. Close observation will also show that occupancy of some of the buildings have changed. The low building directly across the roof of the diner in view 1 and behind the Sobol Bros. sign in view 2 is the Brooklyn Vocational School Annex.\n\nP. L. Sperr\nView 1: October 31, 1927\nView 2: October 11, 1940\n",
